# Currently available plugins (rev3729, ~ End of November 2018)
This page should list the available ZeroNet plugins (that can be found in the `plugin` folder of ZeroNet) along with some description to better document them.
More details are given in the single plugin page.

## AnnounceLocal

## AnnounceShare

## AnnounceZero

## BigFile
This plugin allows upload of big files to zeronet.
The files are chunked and uploaded in pieces.

## Chart

## ContentFilter
Allow block sites based on sha256 hashed address

## Cors

## CryptMessage

## Bootstrapper (default disabled)

## Dnschain (default disabled)

## DonationMessage (default disabled)

## Multiuser (default disabled)
user manager for multiple identities

## StemPort (default disabled)

## UiPassword (default disabled)

## Zeroname-local (default disabled)

## FilePack

## MergerSite

## Newsfeed

## OptionalManager
Plugin to manage optional files

## PeerDb

## Sidebar
Sidebar to display site infos and modify settings, Per-site upload/download bytes statistics, Deny different origin media requests, Allow 10sec to finish query modifications, Websocket display errors to client instead of disconnecting, Allow specify notification id to server-side messages, Track every command response time
